      • size

      • unset

        public void unset()
        Unset the given option or input. This is different from clearing the option in that it will no longer be defined. An option that is cleared but not unset is submitted as an empty list of values to the Web API. An option that is unset are not submitted to the Web API, which leaves the Web API or the Pipeline 2 script free to use a default value.

      • isDefined

        public boolean isDefined()
        Unset the given option or input. This is different from clearing the option in that it will no longer be defined. An option that is cleared but not unset is submitted as an empty list of values to the Web API. An option that is unset are not submitted to the Web API, which leaves the Web API or the Pipeline 2 script free to use a default value.
        Returns:
        True if the argument is defined/set. False otherwise.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Clear the given option or input. This is different from unsetting the option in that it will still be defined. An option that is cleared but not unset is submitted as an empty list of values to the Web API. An option that is unset are not submitted to the Web API, which leaves the Web API or the Pipeline 2 script free to use a default value.
